<subSubSection id="41A20CD1815D1BBB69F5EC945EBEF247" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" type="description">
<paragraph id="102CA9FAF1E06843A6E0CAD679F68B95" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="850019611EB31B7FAF85A6E68D9139F0" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">
Biennial (or perennial?) herb. 
<emphasis id="957E3DACCFFCE26EE04D0083BA8903D3" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Sterile stems</emphasis>
absent. 
<emphasis id="57FEDAE0DA46EF03653B7D35D70FFE94" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Rosette</emphasis>
present during florescence; rosette leaves alternate, broadly obovate, base attenuated and shortly spurred, 0.5-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="317893C97C81EA1EF1AC2EDF95AB114B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-0.7 cm. 
<emphasis id="98C20DBB256AD2B8491DC6775B5C2E7E" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Flowering stems</emphasis>
1 to 3 (-4), erect, slender, 3-7 cm; single stems shoot from rosette centers, others shoot from the rosette leaf axils; lateral proximal leaves sometimes opposite, akin to rosette leaves but smaller, 0.6-0.8 
<normalizedToken id="4E48D287B1D070784A93435AC789332A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.5 cm, base shortly spurred; distal leaves alternate, spatulate-obovate to spatulate-oblanceolate, 0.7-1.2 
<normalizedToken id="C7DCC12835C68DEC4E17BC9C5C1A0563" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.4 cm, apex obtuse, base shortly spurred. 
<emphasis id="8198B631048F812F91EF7BB1E3D167FA" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Cymes</emphasis>
scorpioid, 2 to 3 branched; branches 1 to 2 flowered; bracts obliquely oblanceolate, apex obtuse, 4-9 
<normalizedToken id="C513BF147294EF03E180441A95D564CC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-4 mm. 
<emphasis id="C5BD680E51B58F5C8668AF061CB8CB55" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Sepals</emphasis>
5, lanceolate-oblong, subequal, ca. 2 mm, base shortly spurred, apex obtuse. 
<emphasis id="2A522AAAC6E6C82E2B1F741C8BAEF163" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Petals</emphasis>
5, yellow, broadly lanceolate, ca. 4 mm, apex mucronate. 
<emphasis id="4B7CC940453B7C7893A5E5BFD028C3A0" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Stamens</emphasis>
10; antesepalous one ca. 3 mm; antepetalous one inserted ca. 1 mm above petal base, slightly shorter than the antesepalous stamens. 
<emphasis id="334124E626B3E729EC90236E4807E8DD" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Nectar scales</emphasis>
broadly cuneate, ca. 0.6 
<normalizedToken id="845068D9362AE46D01B9FA7C0A9184BF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4 mm, apex truncate. 
<emphasis id="970F392FF7E33EB7637F07C84543EF6E" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Carpels</emphasis>
erect, lanceolate, ca. 3.5 mm, base connate for ca. 1 mm. 
<emphasis id="D102C46836744CE0520F98E441A89DD7" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Styles</emphasis>
slender, ca. 1 mm. 
<emphasis id="E9D2C481F179A5A150C27381BDA91308" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Follicles</emphasis>
stellately divergent at maturity. 
<emphasis id="488339976897D67916E0B226B7459F11" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Seeds</emphasis>
oblong, ca. 0.6 mm, papillate.
</paragraph>
